This paper discusses the challenges and methods for improving domain robustness in neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of adversarial examples and defensive distillation, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of subword regularization, which is a technique used in neural networks for computer vision, suggesting that cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) may also be a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of noisy channel models, which are commonly used in information theory and communication systems, suggesting that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) may also be a relevant sub-category.
